segments.text: Council Bill 119583 is a council bill to lift a proviso on $150,000 in funding for town hall renovations approved in the 2019 budget.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_01

segments.text: The funds added in the 2019 budget require a public benefit to accompany them, and so we've used the time since the passage and enactment of the 2019 budget and today to have a
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_01

segments.text: negotiation with Town Hall on what that public benefit is.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_01

segments.text: And the agreement was to focus the public benefit on race and equity for community-based organizations.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_01

segments.text: And as a result, Town Hall will
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_01

segments.text: provide up to 50 hours per year of free use of one of their rooms that you can book and make available for events called the Reading Room.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_01

segments.text: And it will be provided to 501c3s, other community-based organizations and community groups, as well as access by city departments for program related to race and equity.
